  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This study is prospectively enrolling a cohort of adolescent patients who present to the
      Emergency Department with acute suicidality.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      This study is prospectively enrolling a cohort of adolescent patients who present to the
      Emergency Department with acute suicidality. The plan is to monitor basic physiologic
      parameters to assess for trends associated with suicidality noninvasively in an objective
      manner beyond subjective questionnaires currently available. Patients will be enrolled if
      presenting to the pediatric emergency department with acute suicidal thoughts or attempt.
      Upon discharge they will be sent home with a noninvasive monitor to track physiologic
      parameters.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
